- Depends on wa-2umk2 (in-tree source ownership — can modify config/mux crates)
- FrankenMux (wa-2dd4s) benefits from WASM plugin panes (like Zellij)
- Ghostty analysis (wa-3bja) may reveal additional extension points
- asupersync (wa-e34d9) provides the async runtime for WASM I/O","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-10T06:52:21.712816Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-02-10T07:31:22.850828Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"wa-3dfxb","depends_on_id":"wa-2umk2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-10T06:52:56.037582Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}"}]}
 {"id":"wa-3dfxb.1","title":"Define ScriptingEngine trait abstraction and multi-engine dispatcher","description":"# Define ScriptingEngine Trait Abstraction

## Why
The dual-runtime strategy (Lua + WASM) needs a common interface so the rest of FrankenTerm doesn't care which engine is running. The ScriptingEngine trait is the abstraction boundary.

## Design

### Core trait
```rust
/// The unified scripting engine interface.
/// Both LuaEngine and WasmEngine implement this.
pub trait ScriptingEngine: Send + Sync + 'static {
    /// Load and evaluate a configuration file, returning structured config.
    fn eval_config(&self, path: &Path) -> Result<TerminalConfiguration>;

    /// Register an event hook. Returns a handle for later removal.
    fn register_hook(&self, event: &str, handler: HookHandler) -> Result<HookId>;

    /// Unregister a previously registered hook.
    fn unregister_hook(&self, id: HookId) -> Result<()>;

    /// Fire an event, calling all registered hooks and collecting actions.
    fn fire_event(&self, event: &str, payload: &dyn ToDynamic) -> Result<Vec<Action>>;

    /// Load an extension from a manifest.
    fn load_extension(&self, manifest: &ExtensionManifest) -> Result<ExtensionId>;

    /// Unload an extension.
    fn unload_extension(&self, id: ExtensionId) -> Result<()>;

    /// Query engine capabilities (for feature detection).
    fn capabilities(&self) -> EngineCapabilities;

    /// Human-readable engine name ("lua-5.4", "wasmtime-28.0", etc.)
    fn engine_name(&self) -> &str;
}
```

### Supporting types
```rust
pub struct HookHandler {
    pub priority: i32,  // Lower = earlier
    pub filter: Option<String>,  // Optional event filter pattern
    // Internal: engine-specific closure/function ref
}

pub struct EngineCapabilities {
    pub supports_async: bool,
    pub supports_filesystem: bool,
    pub supports_network: bool,
    pub sandboxed: bool,
    pub max_memory_bytes: Option<usize>,
    pub max_execution_time: Option<Duration>,
}

pub enum Action {
    SetConfig(String, DynValue),
    SendInput(PaneId, String),
    Log(LogLevel, String),
    Custom(String, DynValue),
}
```

### Multi-engine dispatcher
```rust
pub struct ScriptingDispatcher {
    engines: Vec<Box<dyn ScriptingEngine>>,
    config_engine: usize,  // Index of primary config engine
}
```
The dispatcher tries engines in order for config loading, and fans out events to all engines' hooks.

## Location
- New crate: `frankenterm/scripting/` (or module in config crate, TBD)
- Re-exported from config crate for backward compat

## Files
- frankenterm/scripting/src/lib.rs — trait definitions
- frankenterm/scripting/src/dispatcher.rs — multi-engine dispatcher
- frankenterm/scripting/src/types.rs — Action, HookHandler, etc.
- frankenterm/scripting/Cargo.toml — minimal deps (wezterm-dynamic, anyhow)

## Testing
